#: ../../functions.md:3
msgid "Loading libraries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:5
msgid ""
"To declare functions, start by loading the shared library with "
"`koffi.load(filename)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:14
msgid ""
"This library will be automatically unloaded once all references to it are"
" gone (including all the functions that use it, as described below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:16
msgid ""
"Starting with *Koffi 2.3.20*, you can explicitly unload a library by "
"calling `lib.unload()`. Any attempt to find or call a function from this "
"library after unloading it will crash."
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:19
msgid ""
"On some platforms (such as with the [musl C library on "
"Linux](https://wiki.musl-libc.org/functional-differences-from-glibc.html"
"#Unloading-libraries)), shared libraries cannot be unloaded, so the "
"library will remain loaded and memory mapped after the call to "
"`lib.unload()`."
msgstr ""

