#: ../../functions.md:96
msgid "Call types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:98
msgid "Synchronous calls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:100
msgid ""
"Once a native function has been declared, you can simply call it as you "
"would any other JS function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:109
msgid ""
"For [variadic functions](functions.md#variadic-functions), you msut "
"specificy the type and the value for each additional argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:118
msgid "Asynchronous calls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:120
msgid ""
"You can issue asynchronous calls by calling the function through its "
"async member. In this case, you need to provide a callback function as "
"the last argument, with `(err, res)` parameters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:140
msgid ""
"These calls are executed by worker threads. It is **your responsibility "
"to deal with data sharing issues** in the native code that may be caused "
"by multi-threading."
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:142
msgid ""
"You can easily convert this callback-style async function to a promise-"
"based version with `util.promisify()` from the Node.js standard library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:144
msgid "Variadic functions cannot be called asynchronously."
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:147
msgid ""
"Asynchronous functions run on worker threads. You need to deal with "
"thread safety issues if you share data between threads."
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:149
msgid ""
"Callbacks must be called from the main thread, or more precisely from the"
" same thread as the V8 intepreter. Calling a callback from another thread"
" is undefined behavior, and will likely lead to a crash or a big mess. "
"You've been warned!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:152
msgid "Function pointers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:154
msgid "*New in Koffi 2.4*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:156
msgid "You can call a function pointer in two ways:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:158
msgid "Directly call the function pointer with `koffi.call(ptr, type, ...)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:159
msgid ""
"Decode the function pointer to an actual function with `koffi.decode(ptr,"
" type)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:161
msgid ""
"The example below shows how to call an `int (*)(int, int)` C function "
"pointer both ways, based on the following native C library:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:181
msgid "Call pointer directly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:183
msgid ""
"Use `koffi.call(ptr, type, ...)` to call a function pointer. The first "
"two arguments are the pointer itself and the type of the function you are"
" trying to call (declared with `koffi.proto()` as shown below), and the "
"remaining arguments are used for the call."
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:200
msgid "Decode pointer to function"
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:202
msgid ""
"Use `koffi.decode(ptr, type)` to get back a JS function, which you can "
"then use like any other Koffi function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../functions.md:204
msgid ""
"This method also allows you to perform an [asynchronous call"
"](#asynchronous-calls) with the async member of the decoded function."
msgstr ""

